REQP-1840#1 Warning
RAMB18 async control check  
The RAMB18E1 u_cnn_top/u_conv2/weight_idx_reg_rep has an input control pin u_cnn_top/u_conv2/weight_idx_reg_rep/ENARDEN (net: u_cnn_top/u_conv2/weight_idx_reg_rep_i_1__1_n_0) which is driven by a register (u_cnn_top/u_pool1/done_reg) that has an active asychronous set or reset. This may cause corruption of the memory contents and/or read values when the set/reset is asserted and is not analyzed by the default static timing analysis. It is suggested to eliminate the use of a set/reset to registers driving this RAMB pin or else use a synchronous reset in which the assertion of the reset is timed by default.
Related violations: <none>

